This paper is about using POMDPs to model the attack planning problem in penetration testing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves using intelligent scanning actions, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with testing network security, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
